cabhQos2Mib.name: cabhQos2Mib

revisions.description: Initial revision, published as part of CableHome Specification.

cabhQos2Mib.contactinfo: Kevin Luehrs Postal: Cable Television Laboratories, Inc. 858 Coal Creek Circle Louisville, Colorado 80027 U.S.A. Phone: +1 303-661-9100 Fax: +1 303-661-9199 E-mail: k.luehrs@cablelabs.com; mibs@cablelabs.com
cabhQos2Mib.description: This MIB module supplies parameters for the configuration and monitoring of CableHome QoS capabilities.

cabhQos2SetToFactory.name: cabhQos2SetToFactory
cabhQos2SetToFactory.description: When this object is set to true(1), the PS MUST clear all the entries in cabhQos2PolicyTable and cabhQos2TrafficClassTable. Reading this object always returns false(2).

cabhQos2LastSetToFactory.name: cabhQos2LastSetToFactory
cabhQos2LastSetToFactory.description: The value of sysUpTime when cabhQos2SetToFactory was last set to true. Zero if never reset.

cabhQos2PsIfAttribTable.name: cabhQos2PsIfAttribTable
cabhQos2PsIfAttribTable.description: This table contains interface attributes. It includes the number of media access priorities and number of queues associated with each PS interface in the Residential Gateway.

cabhQos2PsIfAttribEntry.name: cabhQos2PsIfAttribEntry
cabhQos2PsIfAttribEntry.description: Number of media access priorities and number of queues for each PS interface in the Residential Gateway. PS does not need to provide support for entries associated with Aggregated LAN interfaces (ifIndex 255 and 254). The PS WAN interfaces are assigned as ifIndex 1 for Wan Management and ifIndex 2 for Wan Data; both interfaces are indicated in this table as 'WAN interface' with ifIndex 1 as the entry identifier.

cabhQos2PsIfAttribNumPriorities.name: cabhQos2PsIfAttribNumPriorities
cabhQos2PsIfAttribNumPriorities.description: The number of media access priorities supported by this interface.

cabhQos2PsIfAttribNumQueues.name: cabhQos2PsIfAttribNumQueues
cabhQos2PsIfAttribNumQueues.description: The number of queues associated with this interface.

cabhQos2PolicyHolderEnabled.name: cabhQos2PolicyHolderEnabled
cabhQos2PolicyHolderEnabled.description: The value true indicates that the Policy Holder entity is active and advertised in PS UPnP standard discovery mechanisms; false indicates it is disabled.

cabhQos2PolicyAdmissionControl.name: cabhQos2PolicyAdmissionControl
cabhQos2PolicyAdmissionControl.description: Indicates if the QoS Policy Admission Control is enabled or disabled for all the traffic requests.

cabhQos2NumActivePolicyHolder.name: cabhQos2NumActivePolicyHolder
cabhQos2NumActivePolicyHolder.description: Indicates the number of active policy holders the PS have discovered in the LAN. This object includes the PS Policy Holder if active.

cabhQos2PolicyTable.name: cabhQos2PolicyTable
cabhQos2PolicyTable.description: This table contains the operator and user created policies for the management of QoS for applications. PS creates non-persistent entries (of type 'upnp') for the QoS-aware applications and services discovered through UPnP actions in the user part of this table which could be converted to persistent entries by user (of type 'user' or by cable operator of type 'operatorForHomeUserOnly).

cabhQos2PolicyOwner.name: cabhQos2PolicyOwner
cabhQos2PolicyOwner.description: This Index defines the policy creation owner. The entries of type 'upnp' are dynamically created by the PS for the applications, services and devices that it discovers on the LAN with UPnP QoS actions.

cabhQos2PolicyOwnerRuleId.name: cabhQos2PolicyOwnerRuleId
cabhQos2PolicyOwnerRuleId.description: Index for the set of rules related to an owner index.

cabhQos2PolicyRuleOrder.name: cabhQos2PolicyRuleOrder
cabhQos2PolicyRuleOrder.description: The order in which the policy rules are processed within An owner.

cabhQos2PolicyAppDomain.name: cabhQos2PolicyAppDomain
cabhQos2PolicyAppDomain.description: Vendor domain name from the Vendor application name URN.

cabhQos2PolicyServiceProvDomain.name: cabhQos2PolicyServiceProvDomain
cabhQos2PolicyServiceProvDomain.description: The service Provider Service Domain Name from the service Provider URN.

cabhQos2PolicyPortDomain.name: cabhQos2PolicyPortDomain
cabhQos2PolicyPortDomain.description: Domain name from the Port URN.

cabhQos2PolicyPortNumber.name: cabhQos2PolicyPortNumber
cabhQos2PolicyPortNumber.description: Well known IP transport port of the application.

cabhQos2PolicyIpType.name: cabhQos2PolicyIpType
cabhQos2PolicyIpType.description: The type of InetAddress for cabhQos2PolicySrcIp, and cabhQos2PolicyDestIp.

cabhQos2PolicyIpProtocol.name: cabhQos2PolicyIpProtocol
cabhQos2PolicyIpProtocol.description: The IANA-defined IP protocol number representing the IP protocol to match against the IPv4 protocol number or the IPv6 Next- Header number in the packet. '0' means no protocol is specified as matching criteria for policy determination, i.e., QoS policy is irrespective of IP protocol.

cabhQos2PolicySrcIp.name: cabhQos2PolicySrcIp
cabhQos2PolicySrcIp.description: The IP address to match against the packet's source IP address. This may not be a DNS name, but may be an IPv4 or IPv6 prefix.

cabhQos2PolicyDestIp.name: cabhQos2PolicyDestIp
cabhQos2PolicyDestIp.description: The IP address to match against the packet's source IP address. This may not be a DNS name, but may be an IPv4 or IPv6 prefix.

cabhQos2PolicySrcPort.name: cabhQos2PolicySrcPort
cabhQos2PolicySrcPort.description: The value that the layer-4 source port number in the packet must have in order to match this policy entry.

cabhQos2PolicyDestPort.name: cabhQos2PolicyDestPort
cabhQos2PolicyDestPort.description: The value that the layer-4 destination port number in the packet must have in order to match this policy entry.

cabhQos2PolicyTraffImpNum.name: cabhQos2PolicyTraffImpNum
cabhQos2PolicyTraffImpNum.description: The Traffic priority being assigned to this policy. The final packet tagging is determined by 802.1D rules with the priority hierarchy order (highest to lowest priority) as defined in 802.1D-2004 table G-2: 7, 6, 5, 4, 3, 0, 2, 1. Note that traffic type '1' and '2' has lower priority than '0' (best effort).

cabhQos2PolicyUserImportance.name: cabhQos2PolicyUserImportance
cabhQos2PolicyUserImportance.description: The UPnP relative value to determine the allocation or reallocation of resources to multiple streams.

cabhQos2PolicyRowStatus.name: cabhQos2PolicyRowStatus
cabhQos2PolicyRowStatus.description: The status of this conceptual row. All writable objects in this row may be modified at any time. The PS MUST NOT allow creation of new entry or modification to an existing active entry such that the resulting entry is a duplicate entry with respect to the following MIBs in an entry: cabhQos2PolicyAppDomain, cabhQos2PolicyAppNameSnmpAdminString, cabhQos2PolicyServiceProvDomainSnmpAdminString, cabhQos2PolicyServiceName SnmpAdminString, cabhQos2PolicyPortDomain SnmpAdminString, cabhQos2PolicyPortNumber InetPortNumber, cabhQos2PolicyIpType InetAddressType, cabhQos2PolicyIpProtocol Unsigned32, cabhQos2PolicySrcIp InetAddress, cabhQos2PolicyDestIp InetAddress, cabhQos2PolicySrcPort InetPortNumber, cabhQos2PolicyDestPort InetPortNumber, The entries of type 'upnp' are not persistent while others are persistent. The user or the operator can change the 'upnp' entries and in that case the PS MUST change the entry to either 'homeUser' or 'operatorForHomeUser', respectively. The PS MUST NOT change the entries of type 'upnp' to 'operatorOnly'.

cabhQos2TrafficClassTable.name: cabhQos2TrafficClassTable
cabhQos2TrafficClassTable.description: This table contains the Classifiers being configured in the PS as an intermediate QOS device. For matching classifiers the PS processes entries in a sorted manner, first entries with cabhQos2TrafficClassMethod 'static' and then 'dynamic' entries.

cabhQos2TrafficClassEntry.name: cabhQos2TrafficClassEntry
cabhQos2TrafficClassEntry.description: The conceptual row definition of this table. Only entries with cabhQos2TrafficClassMethod 'static' do persist after PS reboot.

cabhQos2TrafficClassMethod.name: cabhQos2TrafficClassMethod
cabhQos2TrafficClassMethod.description: Indicates how this entry have been created. 'static' indicates that the entry has been provisioned via SNMP or related mechanisms like a config file. 'upnp' indicates that the entry was created via UPnP Qos actions.

cabhQos2TrafficClassIdx.name: cabhQos2TrafficClassIdx
cabhQos2TrafficClassIdx.description: The index of this conceptual row entry.

cabhQos2TrafficClassProtocol.name: cabhQos2TrafficClassProtocol
cabhQos2TrafficClassProtocol.description: The IANA IP transport protocol designated for this classifier. '0' means no protocol is specified as matching criteria.

cabhQos2TrafficClassIpType.name: cabhQos2TrafficClassIpType
cabhQos2TrafficClassIpType.description: The type of InetAddress for cabhQos2TrafficClassSrcIp, and cabhQos2TrafficClassDestIp.

cabhQos2TrafficClassSrcIp.name: cabhQos2TrafficClassSrcIp
cabhQos2TrafficClassSrcIp.description: The IP address to match against the packet's source IP address for this classifier. This may not be a DNS name, but may be an IPv4 or IPv6 prefix.

cabhQos2TrafficClassDestIp.name: cabhQos2TrafficClassDestIp
cabhQos2TrafficClassDestIp.description: The IP address to match against the packet's source IP address fro this classifier. This may not be a DNS name, but may be an IPv4 or IPv6 prefix.

cabhQos2TrafficClassSrcPort.name: cabhQos2TrafficClassSrcPort
cabhQos2TrafficClassSrcPort.description: The value that the layer-4 source port number in the packet must have in order to match this classifier entry.

cabhQos2TrafficClassDestPort.name: cabhQos2TrafficClassDestPort
cabhQos2TrafficClassDestPort.description: The value that the layer-4 destination port number in the packet must have in order to match this classifier entry.

cabhQos2TrafficClassImpNum.name: cabhQos2TrafficClassImpNum
cabhQos2TrafficClassImpNum.description: The traffic priority assigned to this classifier and used for the tagging of the packet streams.

cabhQos2TrafficClassRowStatus.name: cabhQos2TrafficClassRowStatus
cabhQos2TrafficClassRowStatus.description: The status of this conceptual row. All writable objects in rows with cabhQosTrafficMethod 'static' may be modified at any time. An SNMP Set to Entries with cabhQosTrafficMethod 'upnp' returns an error 'wrongValue'with the exception of the RowStatus object when set to 'destroy'. An attempt to create an entry via SNMP with cabhQosTrafficMethod UPnP returns error 'wrongValue'.

cabhQos2Compliance.name: cabhQos2Compliance
cabhQos2Compliance.description: The compliance statement for devices that implement CableHome QOS UPnP capabilities.

cabhQos2Group.name: cabhQos2Group
cabhQos2Group.description: Group of objects for CableHome QOS management.

cabhQos2ClassifierGroup.name: cabhQos2ClassifierGroup
cabhQos2ClassifierGroup.description: Group of objects for cableHome QOS Packet classification.
